content: This contribution hasn’t received enough positive votes from the community. The "FASTEST" option has therefore been deactivated.

"If the number area of ​​the parallelogram consists of several digits" doesn't make sense. Even if the area consists of just a single digit, this problem is still expecting you to convert the area into a string and calculate the sum of each character's ASCII code.

✅ Approved the contribution.

"If the number area of ​​the parallelogram consists of several digits": no, it is always the case.
